args: Now shatter like candy between my teeth!\nAah ha ha ha ha!
Are we really gonna die in this\nunsightly way?
Definitely looks like it. How boring...
First you're saved by people who were your\nenemies, and now you're in this scrape?
Did you get infected with weakness in the\nshort time we've been apart? Bwa ha ha!
How feeble of you to be killed by\nsomething such as this. You are weak,\nand weakness must be culled.
You are not worthy to meet my fallen king.
Though you always ridicule others for it,\nyou are actually the weaklings who are\nunsightly and boring.
Nedrick will likely be ashamed that he\never entrusted you with masks.
It is the peak of feeble fecklessness to be\nso resigned while having power.
Or will the two of you continue to\nstruggle hopelessly?
They're running their mouths, but they're\nall just voices in our heads.
But I'm sure they'd say the same thing\nif they could see us the way we are...
Exactly! Plus, I won't be satisfied unless\nwe get her back for this.
We're rebels against the world—\nthe ones who will awaken it.
Our rebellion will never end until we've\nchewed up this world. That's why...
Hrk! We have the disadvantage\nin this situation.
Now that I'm done with the twins, I'll kill\nyou all next! Oh, but quick question:\nDo you prefer PAIN or SUFFERING?
Huh? What's this? A blue butterfly?
I'm detecting high-density mana coming\nfrom the butterfly.\n▷Could that be...?!◁
Okay, what the heck is this?!
Just our way of saying thanks\nfor the candy.
We are Agito, the twin wings that soar to\nfreedom, and none can interfere with it!
How can they transform into this beast\nwithout the power of the mask?!
▷Because we were wrong. The power of\nthe mask stayed with them even after the\nbattle at the Sacred Tree.◁

I surmise their bodies were trying to adapt
to the amplified power of the masks,
which left them temporarily unable to
use their power.
▷But now they've adapted to the\namplified power, which means their\nabilities will be even stronger!◁
Now let's play together! Let's play until\nyou're all in PIECES!

What, you want me to act all impressed
just 'cause you fused? Ha! Not likely!
I'll just let the berserk humans handle
the androids here...
While I kill you damn kids!
That it? How unsightly! Try harder.
(The little brats really have powered up...\nBut I ain't done yet!)
Can't do a daaaarn thing if you can't move,\ncan ya? Now get ready to get dyin'!
According to past combat data, the candy\nis strong against interior impact, but can\nbe destroyed from the outside.
Wait, the androids are interfering now?!\nWhat happened to the berserk humans?!
Changing cartridge. Charging holy water.\nTarget locked...FIRE!
Sorry for being so late, but we've come\nwith holy water from the Halidom! Leave\nthe purification of the townsfolk to us!
Analyzing... If we damage both wings of\nLilith's staff, we can weaken her.
Then we'll pluck those wings right off.\nNow show us the unsightly sight of you\ngroveling, you boring demon!
The wings... Oh, you jerks can NOT\ndo this to me! No way!

I'm gonna tear every last one of you to
pieces—especially you rotten little twins!
So you better be ready, because I'm comin'
back LOADED FOR BEAR!
The berserk villagers have been purified.
I'd like to say that this settles things,\nbut I don't think it does.
With our mutual enemy gone, there is no\nlonger any need for us to be cooperating\nwith those two.
So are we going to play or what?\nI mean, we don't care. Whatever.
Yeah, I'm not done having fun, so we're\ngonna play even if you tell us to stop.

▷Actually, I have a request. From now on,
do you think you two can maybe stop
brutally murdering people and burning
things to the ground?◁
What are you getting at, man?
There's no way these two loonies\nwould ever agree to that.
It's true their spirits are immature and\ncruel, and they go too far in search of\ntheir own desires. But...
▷But they can still think of each other,\nwhich means they have hearts that work\nin there somewhere.◁

▷And if they have hearts, they ought to
understand that freedom is something
shared with everyone, not owned by just
the two of them.◁
You two are beasts who can't be reasoned\nwith, and I should have killed you when\nI had the chance!

This isn't a command. Just a request.
▷I'm sure you two are capable of learning
a different kind of freedom than you've
enjoyed up until now.◁
—Eh heh heh heh!\n—Kyaaaa ha ha ha!
Our freedom is correct, which means\nwe don't need a different one.
Being able to play with and bust whatever\nwe want IS our freedom, and no one else\ncan decide that for us.
But I do kinda like the idea of you asking\nus for something, so we'll listen to half\nof your request.
For a little while at least, the only ones\nwe'll destroy will be people who've\nattacked us.

We're never going to let Lilith off the hook
for making a fool of us—and since she's
got some fellow demons, we'll just destroy
all of 'em together!

But then once all the demons are gone,
it'll be your turn, Laxi. We'll tear you and
every one of your friends at that castle
into teeny tiny pieces.
No use getting mad about it. We made up\nour minds, so that's what we're gonna do.
Also, it was sorta interesting fighting with\nall of you, so it might be nice to play like\nwe're friends every once in a while.
Uh oh. It's gotten pretty dark.\nTime for us to go, Oto.
Their signal is lost, almost as if it is using\nsome kind of stealth functionality. Perhaps\nthis is part of the mask's amplified power.
▷I guess there's no way to come to an\nunderstanding with them, huh?◁
That is a difficult question. However,\nhuman beings are always changing,\nso they should be no exception.
Oh my gosh, did you hear the news?\nWe've got GHOSTS at the Halidom!
And people keep hearing the sounds\nof laughter and footsteps...
And when you go out on adventures,\nit feels like someone is joining you.\nIt's just like an actual horror story!
Hey, I'm an adult, so I'm not even\na little scared.
All right, it's bedtime for good little girls\nand boys. If you're naughty and stay up\nlate, I'm gonna gobble you up!
Honestly, those kids are... Wait, huh?\nWho were those other faces there?
Hey. You. Out doing night patrol?\nIsn't that BORING?
Wait, it's a rule? Ugh. Being tied up by\nthings like that is stifling, which is why...
